snippet.textDisplay: The wine glass with straw looks interesting, but it's also interesting to see half a glass already brings the liquid halfway up the straw, as the weight of the liquid in the glass causes pressure to push it down through the gap and up the straw. So yeah, pretty sure if you filled it up, the 'straw' would leak. If just drinking wine I suppose it would be fine since people fill like half or less of the glass in order to swirl and aerate it a bit, but probably not good as an actual glass substitute in everyday usage for drinking common liquids. So, useful but doesn't really outweigh the niche specific usecase imo. Would be fascinating to see whether the different densities of liquids such as juice as opposed to water, and how they affect the rate of liquid rise up the straw for the same volume, if at all noticeably
